cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with scheduling in wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a framework to model the quality of service requirements, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses stochastic network theory to model the arrival process, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes an optimal scheduling algorithm for allocating data rates to all flows, which involves distributed computing concepts. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper deals with optimizing the rate allocation to meet delay constraints, which falls under the domain of performance analysis.
